# Lead & Deal Creation — POSP Only

**Only POSP users may create new leads and new deals.** Managers (DM, ASM, RH,
ZH, National Head, Super Admin) may **view, filter, export, and update** pipeline
records in their territory — but they do not originate leads or deals on behalf of
agents.

## Allowed

| Action | Who |
|--------|-----|
| `POST /api/leads` — create lead | **POSP only** |
| `POST /api/deals` — create deal / quote | **POSP only** |
| `GET/PATCH` leads & deals | Managers + POSP (scoped) |
| `POST /api/leads/:id/convert` | ASM+ (promotes an existing lead — not a blank create) |
| `DELETE /api/deals/:id` | ASM+ |

## POSP create rules

- A POSP deal is always tied to **their own** `pospId` (server-enforced via
  `resolvePospScope`).
- POSP creates leads for customers in their book; managers do not log prospects
  for agents.

## What must NOT be built or re-enabled

- No "+ New Lead" / "+ New Deal" buttons for manager roles
- No manager "issue on behalf of POSP" or "Self" deal creation flows
- No Super Admin POSP picker on **create** deal modal
- Do not widen `POST /api/deals` or `POST /api/leads` to `@MinRole(DM)` or ASM+

Managers coach and review pipeline data; **field agents own creation**.

## UI surfaces

| Surface | Create button |
|---------|---------------|
| `/leads` | POSP only |
| `/deals` | POSP only |
| `/dashboard` | POSP only (`+ New Deal`) |

If asked to let managers create leads/deals, explain this rule — do not implement it.
